Connect GitHub Repository:

Log in to Render and create a new web service.
Connect your GitHub repository where your Streamlit application code resides.
Choose a Unique Website Name:

Select a unique name for your website during the setup process.
Prepare requirements.txt:

Create a requirements.txt file in your repository.
List the dependencies your app needs (streamlit, numpy, xgboost).
Deployment:

Render will automatically fetch your code from GitHub.
It will install the specified dependencies (streamlit, numpy, xgboost).
Deployment begins after configuration, ensuring your app is up and running on Render.
Access Your Application:

Once deployed, your Streamlit app will be accessible via a unique Render URL.
By following these steps, you can swiftly deploy and manage your Streamlit application with its required dependencies on Render.
